<DOC><DOCNO> AP880319-0073 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-19-88 1040EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Rain     03-19 0101</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Rain,0103</SECOND><HEAD>100 Injured in Rain</HEAD><DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Heavy wind and rain lashed theBangladesh capital of Dhaka, flattening houses, uprooting trees andplunging the city of 4 million into darkness, police said Saturday.   At least 100 people were reported injured in the storm, whichhit late Friday, hospital officials said. Doctors said that 10people were in critical condition.   Police said the storm, with winds as high as 36 mph, rippedthrough the city. Hardest hit were suburban areas, where mud andstraw huts collapsed, they said.   Efforts were under way to restore electricity and telephoneservices.</TEXT></DOC>